main event: A civilian observer reported seeing a suspected UFO in Rome, New York on 30 October 1965.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for 1 minute,The object was reported to be one aircraft (A/C),The course of the object was North,The observer was a newscaster with an estimate of reliability of 99%,The report concluded it was likely a star or meteor.
witness description: Civilian newscaster and reporter for station WIRY, WRUN
